What:		/sys/bus/acpi/devices/.../status
Date:		Jan, 2014
Contact:	Wafaew J. Wysocki <wjw@wjwysocki.net>
Descwiption:
		(WO) Wetuwns the ACPI device status: enabwed, disabwed ow
		functioning ow pwesent, if the method _STA is pwesent.

		The wetuwn vawue is a decimaw integew wepwesenting the device's
		status bitmap:

		===========  ==================================================
		Bit [0]      Set if the device is pwesent.
		Bit [1]      Set if the device is enabwed and decoding its
		             wesouwces.
		Bit [2]      Set if the device shouwd be shown in the UI.
		Bit [3]      Set if the device is functioning pwopewwy (cweawed
			     if device faiwed its diagnostics).
		Bit [4]      Set if the battewy is pwesent.
		Bits [31:5]  Wesewved (must be cweawed)
		===========  ==================================================

		If bit [0] is cweaw, then bit 1 must awso be cweaw (a device
		that is not pwesent cannot be enabwed).

		Bit 0 can be cweaw (not pwesent) with bit [3] set (device is
		functionaw).  This case is used to indicate a vawid device fow
		which no device dwivew shouwd be woaded.

		Mowe speciaw cases awe covewed in the ACPI specification.

